&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Solutions Architecture (SA) org aims to be a destination pre-sales organization of world-class technical sellers who set and raise the bar in our interactions with Stripe users. Our goal is to drive Stripe&#39;s long-term revenue growth as trusted technical advisors to users and partners and reliable voice of the user to Stripe Product. The Solutions Architecture Strategic Programs team is a small, high-impact team within SA that partners with global SA leadership to design and deliver programs that address the org&#39;s most strategic priorities (i.e. &quot;Big Rocks&quot;) and time-sensitive business challenges. Our team delivers efficiency and leverage to the SA org by designing programs that 1) make it less frictionful for SAs to deliver user impact and 2) scale best practices to drive the broadest possible global impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an SA Program Manager, you will independently own and drive programs that raise the user-facing excellence and operational effectiveness of the global SA org. You will operate with significant autonomy—scoping ambiguous problems, aligning diverse stakeholders, and driving complex initiatives from strategy through delivery and iteration. Within SA, you&#39;ll partner with SA leadership and SA business partners (e.g. Strategy &amp;amp; Operations, Enablement, Recruiting, People) and a broad set of cross-functional stakeholders (Product Marketing, Field Marketing, Professional Services, Alliance and Channel Partners) to define and roll out global standards of SA user-facing and operational excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently scope, design, deliver, and iterate on high-priority global programs that address SA&#39;s most strategic priorities, owning outcomes end-to-end with minimal oversight&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with SA leadership and SA Enablement to define and scale repeatable frameworks and shared standards of pre-sales excellence by segment and motion and drive adoption through manager training and coaching&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use data to identify organizational gaps, set program priorities, measure impact, and build the case for investment or change across SA leadership and cross-functional partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead change management planning and execution for org-wide programs — including communication, enablement, and operational rigor — ensuring SA managers and ICs adopt new behaviors durably&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigate competing priorities across a broad GTM stakeholder map — including Sales, Marketing, Professional Services, Developer Relations, and Channel partners — to align cross-functional teams around programs that drive measurable improvement in SA effectiveness and user impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a resource and thought partner to SA leadership and peers, sharing knowledge, identifying and raising risks early, and contributing to a higher collective bar for program design and change management in the org&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in GTM program management, business operations, management consulting, or a related discipline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of independently leading complex, cross-functional global programs from scoping through delivery in fast-moving, ambiguous environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong data fluency — able to synthesize data from multiple sources, develop independent hypotheses, and translate insights into clear decisions and recommendations for senior audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience leading change management for large organizations, including communication planning, stakeholder alignment, and adoption measurement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled at influencing cross-functional stakeholders without direct authority across all levels, from individual contributors to executives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills; consistently sets a high bar for clarity, concision, and audience-appropriate framing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working within or directly supporting a Sales or technical pre-sales organization — familiarity with how field teams operate, how deals move, and what drives behavior change in a field org&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building or codifying GTM playbooks, sales excellence frameworks, or motion-specific best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing and driving field enablement programs with measurable adoption outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with or alongside developer relations, partner, or channel organizations in a GTM context&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in fintech, payments, or SaaS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Salesforce, Gong, or similar GTM tooling and data platforms such as Looker or Tableau&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Who we are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Stripe&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies-from the world&#39;s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups-use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the Adaptive Pricing team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is building a global payments and treasury network, and the Adaptive Pricing team sits at the heart of Global Selling-focused on helping businesses optimize how they sell across borders.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;One of the hardest problems in global commerce is pricing. Businesses must navigate different currencies, foreign exchange dynamics, setting proper price points, aligning prices with local standards, and unlocking local payment methods-all while maintaining a seamless buyer experience. Getting this wrong means lost revenue, abandoned carts, and failed payments.&lt;br&gt;To solve this, we built Adaptive Pricing-one of the fastest growing products ever launched at Stripe. Adaptive Pricing automatically presents customers with localized prices in their currency, handles all FX conversion behind the scenes, and unlocks local payment methods across 150+ countries-all with zero integration effort from the business. The result: businesses see an average of 17.8% higher revenue, significantly higher conversion, and improved authorization rates.&lt;br&gt;Adaptive Pricing is already used by over 500,000 businesses globally, processes payments in 150+ countries, and has processed billions in cross-border volume. And we&#39;re just getting started-there is an enormous amount of surface area still to build across subscriptions, full-funnel localization, new payment methods, and intelligent pricing strategies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team is scrappy, moves fast, and punches well above its weight.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own the product strategy, roadmap, and execution for Adaptive Pricing Growth. You&#39;ll be responsible for making Adaptive Pricing the obvious, default choice for every business selling across borders-expanding its capabilities, deepening its intelligence, and scaling its adoption.&lt;br&gt;You will work at the intersection of complex money movement, foreign exchange, machine learning, and developer experience. You will need to go extremely deep to understand the full complexity of global pricing-from FX risk and regulatory compliance to consumer psychology and local payment ecosystems-and translate that into elegant, simple product experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the end-to-end product strategy for Adaptive Pricing Growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deeply understand the problem space-currencies, FX, local payment methods, regional regulations, consumer behavior-and use that knowledge to drive high-conviction product decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set an ambitious roadmap and drive execution with a scrappy, high-velocity team across Engineering, Design, Data Science, and GTM.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the best seller and marketer for the product-work closely with Sales and GTM to drive adoption, handle objections, create pitch materials, and close strategic accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use data rigorously to identify opportunities, measure impact, and prioritize ruthlessly. Analyze conversion funnels, authorization rates, revenue lift, and retention metrics to drive the roadmap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Break down complex systems into functional pieces-decompose the end-to-end pricing problem into tractable product surfaces and ship them incrementally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion the merchant and consumer experience-obsess over making the product beautiful, simple, and delightful despite the underlying complexity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate deeply with cross-functional teams including Engineering, Design, Data Science, Sales, Account Management, Marketing, Risk, and Treasury.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discover new parts of the business (new surfaces, new geographies, new segments) and lead them from nascent stages to maturity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Who you are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are a deeply technical, scrappy, data-driven PM who obsesses over solving problems end to end. You don&#39;t stop at the surface, you go deep to understand every layer of complexity and use that understanding to build products that are both powerful and elegant. You care about craft and beauty in everything you ship, even when the underlying systems are fiendishly complex.&lt;br&gt;You are AI native, you thoughtfully apply AI across your own work and think deeply about how AI can make our products smarter and more powerful. You act like a developer: you can read code, think in systems, and engage credibly with engineers on architecture and tradeoffs.&lt;br&gt;You display extreme ownership. You treat the product as your business-caring deeply about its success, its users, and its growth. You are the kind of person who will get on a call with a merchant to understand their pain, write a SQL query to validate a hypothesis, and mock up a solution in the same afternoon.&lt;br&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of experience in product management or engineering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deeply technical-can think and act like a developer. Comfortable reading code, engaging on architecture decisions, and understanding complex distributed systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scrappy and high-ownership-treats the product as their own business, does whatever it takes to make it succeed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data-driven-can write SQL, build dashboards, analyze funnels, and use data to make decisions and set priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;User-obsessed-spends time with users, synthesizes feedback, and translates insights into product direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cares about craft and beauty-holds a high bar for product quality, design, and user experience even in technically complex domains.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Obsesses over solving the problem end to end-not satisfied with partial solutions or leaving loose ends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willing to go extremely deep to understand all the complexities of the product, the domain, and the competitive landscape.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with Sales and GTM teams-can act as the best seller and marketer for the product, tell a compelling story, and drive adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI native-thoughtfully applies AI across their own work and our products to ship faster and build smarter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to break down complex problems and systems into functional, shippable pieces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills with a talent for precise articulations of customer problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has the ability to thrive with a high level of autonomy and responsibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with complex money movement, regulated spaces, or foreign exchange.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building products that operate across multiple currencies, countries, or regulatory environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building brand new products or working in a startup-like environment within a larger company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with pricing strategy, marketplace dynamics, or fintech infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting product market research and building buy-in for product ideas from internal stakeholders and leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with machine learning teams to build intelligent, data-driven product features.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;In-office expectations&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Office-assigned Stripes in most of our locations are currently expected to spend at least 50% of the time in a given month in their local office or with users. This expectation may vary depending on role, team and location. For example, Stripes in Stripe Delivery Center roles in Mexico City, Mexico, Bengaluru, India, and Dublin, Ireland work 100% from the office. Also, some teams have greater in-office attendance requirements, to appropriately support our users and workflows, which the hiring manager will discuss. This approach helps strike a balance between bringing people together for in-person collaboration and learning from each other, while supporting flexibility when possible.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Who we are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Stripe&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies-from the world&#39;s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups-use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the Local Processor Acquiring team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is building a global payments and treasury network-and Local Processor Acquiring (LPA) is how we&#39;re rapidly extending that network into the world&#39;s fastest-growing markets. The LPA team sits within Global Selling, focused on enabling businesses to accept payments from billions of consumers worldwide without needing to set up local operations.&lt;br&gt;The problem we&#39;re solving is fundamental: the most important payment methods in emerging markets-Korean wallets, PIX in Brazil, UPI in India, QRIS in Indonesia-require local acquiring capabilities that historically took years of work and infrastructure investment to build. Meanwhile, businesses are scaling globally at unprecedented speed and can&#39;t wait.&lt;br&gt;LPA changes the equation entirely. By partnering with best-in-class local processors, we can launch a new market in weeks rather than years-delivering local payment methods, higher authorization rates, and dramatically better conversion for cross-border businesses. Since launching in South Korea, we&#39;ve seen users grow their daily KRW transaction count by over 200% and our data shows &amp;gt;6% increase in conversion uplift when local payment methods are enabled.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own and drive the product strategy, roadmap, and execution for Local Processor Acquiring, defining how Stripe expands into new markets at unprecedented speed. You&#39;ll be responsible for building a product that makes local payment methods from emerging markets as seamless and reliable as any other payment method on Stripe, while navigating complex regulatory environments, partner relationships, and deeply different local payment ecosystems.&lt;br&gt;This role sits at the intersection of global strategy, complex money movement, partner management, and developer experience. You will need to go extremely deep-understanding the nuances of each market&#39;s regulations, payment methods, consumer behaviors, and technical constraints-then translate that complexity into elegant product experiences that work for businesses of all sizes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the end-to-end product strategy for LPA across multiple markets-from partner selection and integration architecture to buyer UX, merchant activation, and product interoperability with Connect, Billing, Radar, and Terminal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deeply understand each market&#39;s payment ecosystem-local payment methods, regulatory requirements, consumer preferences, and competitive dynamics-and use that knowledge to drive prioritization and sequencing decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set an ambitious roadmap and drive execution with a scrappy, high-velocity team across Engineering, Partnerships, Legal, Risk, and GTM. Break down the massive surface area of &quot;launch a country&quot; into tractable, shippable pieces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the best seller and marketer for the product-work directly with Sales to close strategic accounts, handle objections, build pitch materials, and drive adoption across existing Stripe users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use data rigorously to measure impact and prioritize. Analyze conversion uplift, authorization rates, PIV growth, and margin to determine where to invest next and how to demonstrate ROI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own partner relationships from a product perspective-define requirements, set performance SLAs, and drive partners to deliver experiences consistent with Stripe&#39;s quality bar.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion the buyer and merchant experience-obsess over reducing redirects, improving checkout flows, and delivering conversion outcomes that match or exceed direct integrations, even when operating through partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigate complex regulatory and compliance landscapes across multiple jurisdictions. Work closely with Legal, Policy, and Risk to find creative solutions that unlock markets while maintaining compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate deeply with cross-functional teams including Engineering, Design, Partnerships, Legal, Risk, Sales, Account Management, and Operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discover new markets and segments (domestic acquiring, global platforms, Connect use cases) and lead them from nascent stages to maturity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Who you are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are a deeply technical, scrappy, data-driven PM who obsesses over solving problems end to end. You thrive in ambiguity-taking a complex, multi-market, multi-partner problem and breaking it down into clear milestones and shippable increments. You go deep to understand the regulatory constraints, the money flows, the partner dynamics, and the buyer psychology in each market, and you use that understanding to make high-conviction decisions quickly.&lt;br&gt;You care about craft and beauty-even when the underlying systems involve redirects, partner handoffs, and regulatory disclosures, you hold a high bar for the end-to-end experience. You believe that &quot;good enough for a partner integration&quot; is not good enough for Stripe.&lt;br&gt;You are AI native-you thoughtfully apply AI across your own work and think deeply about how AI can accelerate our ability to launch markets, build integrations, and scale operations. You act like a developer: you can read code, think in systems, and engage credibly with engineers on architecture and tradeoffs.&lt;br&gt;You display extreme ownership. You treat LPA as your business-caring deeply about its growth, its users, and its impact on Stripe&#39;s global footprint. You&#39;re the kind of person who will get on a call with a user in a different timezone, dig into a partner&#39;s API docs, write a SQL query to validate conversion hypotheses, and draft a launch plan in the same day.&lt;br&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
