&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of experience in product management or engineering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deeply technical-can think and act like a developer. Comfortable reading code, engaging on architecture decisions, and understanding complex distributed systems and money flows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scrappy and high-ownership-treats the product as their own business, does whatever it takes to make it succeed across multiple markets simultaneously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data-driven-can write SQL, analyze conversion funnels, measure partner performance, and use data to prioritize markets and features.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;User-obsessed-spends time with merchants and buyers, synthesizes feedback across segments, and translates insights into product direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cares about craft and beauty-holds a high bar for product quality and user experience even when operating through partner integrations and navigating regulatory constraints.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Obsesses over solving the problem end to end-from partner integration to buyer checkout to merchant dashboard to settlement and payouts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willing to go extremely deep to understand the complexities of each market-regulations, payment ecosystems, consumer behavior, partner capabilities, and competitive dynamics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with Sales and GTM teams-can act as the best seller and marketer for the product, tell a compelling story about market expansion, and drive adoption with strategic accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI native-thoughtfully applies AI across their own work and our products to ship faster and operate more efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to break down complex problems and systems into functional, shippable pieces-comfortable sequencing work across multiple markets and segments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills with a talent for precise articulations of customer problems and clear strategic narratives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has the ability to thrive with a high level of autonomy and responsibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with complex money movement, regulated spaces, or foreign exchange-particularly across multiple jurisdictions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing external partnerships (processors, PSPs, acquirers, or other financial infrastructure partners) where product quality depends on partner performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building products in emerging markets or navigating diverse regulatory environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building brand new products or working in a startup-like environment within a larger company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with payments infrastructure, local payment methods, or cross-border commerce.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with Connect/marketplace models or multi-sided platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting product market research and building buy-in for product ideas from internal stakeholders and leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
